<br>
I don't see how multiple characters on one account is going to hurt much of anything really...<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>For every jackass 14 year old who has to beg for the money to get *one* EQ account...Could you imagine them convincing their parents to give them the money for two?<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--> <br>
<br>
<br>
First off, as far as 13-14 year old kids, they're never gonna be in the upper quotient of players anyhow, and if they are, if they are that bad, they will have ruined their reputation with a small server population like ours and chances for further advancement will be dim.... as far as Roleplay, your going to have that issue regardless of if the person has 1 or 10 characters.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>Anything that cuts down on the twinks/PLing/etc is a good thing in my book. It is really hard to 100% prevent anything. Where there is a will there is a way.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
As far as Twinking, PL'ing, players who do that, probably a good three out of four, are probably not there to roleplay, so getting into your roleplay business shouldn't be an issue... as far as I see it, if ya have the means to do it, thats your business, no one has the right to tell someone how they manange their character leveling or gear, they pay their 12.95 a month just like we all do.<br>
<br>
If I had a second character, it would probably be for class experiments and such, least on the same account, because you can't dual box two characters on the same account, so self powerleveling would be impossible, and gear transfers would require help, so I find it hard to see how this would hurt the server in general.<br>
<br>
Someones right to try to rule peoples fun on this server with an iron fist is just wrong.  I feel as long as no one is in violation of the rules Sony put out for the game, then so what? doesn't really matter to me.<br>
